@node MAIN "Physical objects handled by ASense"

    This guide is an auxiliary part of ASense package.It describes
  the individual surrounding stars in great and up-to-date details
  from the @{b}astronomical@{ub} point of view.

    For curious amateur astronomers, @{i}some astrological notes were
  also given separately at the ends of pages@{ui}.Feel free to read them.

  @{"Stars" link ASENSE-SELECT-STARS} (detailed analysis of stars)

@{b}@{u}Acknoweldgements@{uu}@{ub}:
  - This research has made use of the SIMBAD database, operated at CDS,
    Strasbourg, France.

@endnode

/// Stars
@node ASENSE-SELECT-STARS "ASense - Select: Stars"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV MAIN
@NEXT MAIN
@{b}@{u}Stars@{uu}@{ub}: Shiny dots across the night sky, the skeleton of heavens.

    These pages describe the individual stellar systems from astronomical
  point of view.Their evolutionary path, status, mechanism of their work.

  @{b}@{u}Repellant note@{uu}@{ub}:

    "@{i}If you wonder where are you, you are definitely here;
     If you wonder why, that puzzles me to...
     This place was empty before you came;
     It will be empty again after you leave...@{ui}"

     Unfortunately, no one has ever bothered to write this guide...

     @{b}But, please, come again in a version '@{i}next@{ui}'.
     Rich literature may emerge...@{ub}

@endnode
